This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with video analysis and action recognition. The use of deep learning and dense trajectories also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the use of rank pooling and temporal evolution encoding could suggest it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. The paper also involves feature extraction and encoding, which could suggest it belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper involves performance evaluation and comparison, which could suggest it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category.
